reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are tissues in bulk
reviews.reviewText: I like the fact that you can buy multiple boxes of tissues. I share some w/family, keep some in my van and use for makeup, wiping noses (animal or humans) and of course blowing my own nose. The tissues are not name brand, but the multiple boxes allow me to have tissues wherever I need them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Small, not soft, and VERY THIN.
reviews.reviewText: I bought these tissues--six boxes--as everyone in my family has a cold. They are worthless for that purpose, however. The tissues are tiny, not soft, and very thin--not strong enough for even one blowing of the nose. I will use them for removing my eye-makeup but will not purchase any more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These tissues are very thin - you have to use at least 2 when blowing your nose! Not worth it! Smaller than the typical tissues too!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 21, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Decent Kleenex's. Not the top brand but they worked to send to school with the kids. Not as soft as I was hoping, but for the price, it works.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars They are Small Boxes But do The Job
reviews.reviewText: I Bought these as I needed something quick. They are small in size and not my normal larger box size. I am so surprised how expensive tissues have become. I have allergies and go through tissues quick so these will be used up quickly. It served it's purpose. I need to look into bulk next time
